If we check…

942
01:20:01,969 --> 01:20:05,764
How did they explain what you
do remember? The gun and stuff?

943
01:20:08,642 --> 01:20:10,644
John G was clever.

944
01:20:11,019 --> 01:20:12,813
He was clever.

945
01:20:12,938 --> 01:20:17,860
He took the dead man's gun and
replaced it with the sap he hit me with.

946
01:20:17,985 --> 01:20:22,072
He left my gun and the getaway car.
He gave the police a complete package.

947
01:20:22,197 --> 01:20:26,869
They found the sap with my blood on it
in the dead man's hand.

948
01:20:26,994 --> 01:20:29,371
And they only found my gun.

949
01:20:29,496 --> 01:20:32,332
They didn't need to look for anybody else.

950
01:20:32,666 --> 01:20:36,295
I was the only guy who disagreed
with the facts and I had brain damage.

951
01:20:36,795 --> 01:20:39,214
The cops are not gonna believe
someone in my condition.

952
01:20:39,965 --> 01:20:44,136
Leonard. You can stay here
for a couple of days if it will help you.

953
01:20:44,761 --> 01:20:46,805
Oh, thanks.

954
01:20:46,972 --> 01:20:51,518
I have to go back to work,
so, um, just make yourself at home.

955
01:20:51,643 --> 01:20:54,062
You can watch TV or have some food.

956
01:20:54,146 --> 01:20:56,690
Whatever you want, OK?
Make yourself at home.

957
01:20:56,815 --> 01:20:58,317
One thing.

958
01:21:01,653 --> 01:21:06,283
- Something to remember you by.
- My name is Natalie.

959
01:21:07,826 --> 01:21:09,870
Natalie.

960
01:21:36,897 --> 01:21:38,315
<font color="#40a040">[door opens]</font>

961
01:21:41,902 --> 01:21:43,904
- What's wrong?
- Somebody's come already.

962
01:21:44,196 --> 01:21:46,323
<font color="#40a040">[phone rings]</font>

963
01:21:49,701 --> 01:21:51,703
<font color="#40a040">[phone rings]</font>

964
01:21:54,081 --> 01:21:56,083
<font color="#40a040">[ringing stops]</font>

965
01:22:28,866 --> 01:22:30,534
<font color="#40a040">[phone rings]</font>

966
01:22:33,203 --> 01:22:36,290
- On the house.
- Thanks.

967
01:22:38,083 --> 01:22:39,418
<font color="#40a040">[laughs]</font>

968
01:22:40,627 --> 01:22:44,548
My, you really do have a problem.
Just like that cop said.

969
01:22:44,673 --> 01:22:47,968
- Hm?
- Your condition.

970
01:22:48,844 --> 01:22:51,054
Well, nobody's perfect.

971
01:22:51,889 --> 01:22:55,559
What's the last thing
that you do remember?

972
01:22:58,729 --> 01:23:00,814
- My wife.
- That's sweet.

973
01:23:00,939 --> 01:23:01,773
Dying.

974
01:23:03,734 --> 01:23:06,153
I remember my wife dying.

975
01:23:09,823 --> 01:23:12,701
Let me, um, get you another one.

976
01:23:12,826 --> 01:23:14,745
I think this one's dusty.

977
01:23:19,041 --> 01:23:21,919
Why are you calling me?
What do you want?

978
01:23:22,044 --> 01:23:25,506
I know you're a cop. What do you want?
Have I done something wrong?

979
01:23:25,839 --> 01:23:28,258
I don't know, something bad, maybe.

980
01:23:29,718 --> 01:23:32,137
Look, why are you asking me?
I can't remember what I've done.

981
01:23:32,262 --> 01:23:34,264
You wouldn't believe me anyway.

982
01:23:34,389 --> 01:23:37,309
Because of my condition, you don't
believe someone with this condition.

983
01:23:37,434 --> 01:23:40,103
Nobody believed Sammy!
I didn't even fucking believe Sammy!

984
01:23:40,979 --> 01:23:42,981
Ferdy's bar.

985
01:23:45,150 --> 01:23:47,653
Come by after. Natalie.

986
01:24:02,626 --> 01:24:04,545
- A beer, please.
- What do you want?

987
01:24:04,670 --> 01:24:05,629
A beer, please.

988
01:24:05,754 --> 01:24:08,131
You can't just waltz in here
dressed like that and ask for a beer.

989
01:24:08,215 --> 01:24:10,551
- What, is there a dress code?
- Why are you here?

990
01:24:10,676 --> 01:24:13,595
- I'm meeting someone called Natalie.
- Well, that's me.

991
01:24:13,720 --> 01:24:16,390
Yeah, we met before, right?

992
01:24:17,307 --> 01:24:19,518
- Then why am I here?
- I don't know, why don't you tell me?

993
01:24:19,601 --> 01:24:21,645
I don't remember.
I have no short-term memory.

994
01:24:21,728 --> 01:24:23,522
Oh, you're that memory guy.

995
01:24:23,647 --> 01:24:27,359
- How do you know about me?
- My boyfriend told me about you.

996
01:24:27,484 --> 01:24:31,363
- Oh, yeah? Who's your boyfriend?
- Jimmy Grants. Do you know him?

997
01:24:32,614 --> 01:24:33,991
No.

998
01:24:34,116 --> 01:24:39,413
He knows you. He told me about you.
He said you were staying at the Discount.

999
01:24:39,496 --> 01:24:42,791
In fact, a cop came by earlier
and was looking for you.

1000
01:24:42,916 --> 01:24:45,002
Said he was looking for a guy
who can't remember anything,…

1001
01:24:45,127 --> 01:24:47,129
… wouldn't know how he'd got here
or what he'd done.

1002
01:24:47,254 --> 01:24:49,131
I get a lot of guys round here like that.

1003
01:24:49,256 --> 01:24:53,677
Chronic alcoholism
is one cause of short-term memory loss.

1004
01:24:55,429 --> 01:24:58,473
- Are you Teddy?
- No, my name's Leonard.

1005
01:24:58,599 --> 01:25:00,684
- Did Teddy send you?
- I don't know.

1006
01:25:01,310 --> 01:25:03,353
What's happened to Jimmy?

1007
01:25:03,437 --> 01:25:07,149
- I don't know that, either. Sorry.
- You don't remember anything?

1008
01:25:07,274 --> 01:25:10,819
You don't remember where you've been
or what you've just done?

1009
01:25:10,944 --> 01:25:14,406
I can't make new memories.
Everything just fades.

1010
01:25:14,573 --> 01:25:17,284
- Then why did you come here?
- I found this in my pocket.

1011
01:25:20,621 --> 01:25:22,706
Your pocket?

1012
01:25:37,971 --> 01:25:39,348
<font color="#40a040">[man hawks]</font>

1013
01:25:47,105 --> 01:25:49,900
Bar bet. Care to contribute?

1014
01:25:50,025 --> 01:25:52,444
- No, thanks.
- It's for a lot of money.

1015
01:25:52,861 --> 01:25:56,740
Come on. Proceeds are going to charity.
Help me out.

1016
01:26:02,079 --> 01:26:04,081
<font color="#40a040">[hawks]</font>

1017
01:26:08,126 --> 01:26:09,920
Thank you.

1018
01:26:26,854 --> 01:26:29,940
- On the house.
- Thanks.

1019
01:26:30,816 --> 01:26:32,818
<font color="#40a040">[man laughs]</font>

1020
01:26:33,819 --> 01:26:37,281
It's completely fucked
because nobody believes you.

1021
01:26:37,322 --> 01:26:41,034
It's amazing what a little brain damage
will do for your credibility.

1022
01:26:41,159 --> 01:26:43,453
I guess it's poetic justice
for not believing Sammy.

1023
01:26:43,537 --> 01:26:48,333
You know the truth about my condition,
officer? You don't know anything.

1024
01:26:48,458 --> 01:26:53,505
You feel angry, you don't know why.
You feel guilty, you have no idea why.

1025
01:26:53,630 --> 01:26:57,092
You could do anything and not have
the faintest idea ten minutes later.

1026
01:26:57,217 --> 01:27:00,179
Like Sammy.
What if I'd done something like Sammy?

1027
01:27:00,262 --> 01:27:04,183
I didn't tell you?
What happened to Sammy and his wife?

1028
01:27:04,308 --> 01:27:06,435
She came to see me at my office.

1029
01:27:06,518 --> 01:27:11,440
I didn't tell her what I really thought
but I never said that he was faking.

1030
01:27:11,565 --> 01:27:13,734
Just that his condition was mental,
not physical.

1031
01:27:13,817 --> 01:27:16,445
I found out later that she went home
and gave Sammy his final exam.

1032
01:27:18,322 --> 01:27:21,116
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1033
01:27:37,174 --> 01:27:40,219
She knew beyond a doubt
that he loved her,

1034
01:27:40,344 --> 01:27:43,013
so she found a way to test him.

1035
01:27:55,025 --> 01:27:58,570
Sammy? It's time for my shot.

1036
01:27:59,571 --> 01:28:01,573
Hm.

1037
01:28:08,914 --> 01:28:12,626
- She really thought she'd call his bluff.
- There you go.

1038
01:28:12,751 --> 01:28:17,422
Or she just didn't want to live with
the things she'd put him through.

1039
01:28:26,181 --> 01:28:27,558
Sammy?

1040
01:28:29,768 --> 01:28:31,144
It's time for my shot.

1041
01:28:37,359 --> 01:28:39,111
It won't hurt.

1042
01:29:22,988 --> 01:29:26,241
She went into a coma
and never recovered.

1043
01:29:26,366 --> 01:29:29,578
Sammy couldn't understand
or explain what happened.

1044
01:29:29,703 --> 01:29:30,662
Oh!

1045
01:29:31,830 --> 01:29:36,251
He's been in a home ever since.
He doesn't even know his wife is dead.

1046
01:29:36,376 --> 01:29:39,713
I was wrong about Sammy
and I was wrong about his wife.

1047
01:29:39,796 --> 01:29:43,967
She wasn't interested in the money.
She needed to understand his problem.

1048
01:29:44,092 --> 01:29:47,763
His brain didn't respond to conditioning
but he wasn't a con man.

1049
01:29:47,888 --> 01:29:51,266
And when she looked into his eyes,
she thought he could be the same person.

1050
01:29:51,391 --> 01:29:53,435
When I looked into his eyes,
I thought I saw recognition.

1051
01:29:53,560 --> 01:29:55,562
Now I know you fake it.

1052
01:29:55,687 --> 01:29:58,732
If you think you're supposed to recognise
somebody, you pretend to.

1053
01:29:58,857 --> 01:30:02,402
You bluff it to get a pat on the head
from the doctors.

1054
01:30:02,528 --> 01:30:05,572
You bluff it to seem less of a freak.

1055
01:30:07,324 --> 01:30:09,326
What drug dealer?

1056
01:30:10,160 --> 01:30:12,162
<font color="#40a040">[tyres squeal]</font>

1057
01:30:34,935 --> 01:30:38,063
- Hey, Lenny, how you doing?
- It's private back here.

1058
01:30:38,146 --> 01:30:41,149
- It's OK, we know each other. Right, kid?
- How did you know I was in here?

1059
01:30:41,233 --> 01:30:43,235
The Jag's out front.

1060
01:30:43,318 --> 01:30:46,321
What are you still doing here, Lenny?
There's plenty of tattoo parlours up north.

1061
01:30:46,405 --> 01:30:49,908
I guess I wanted to get something down
before it slipped my mind.

1062
01:30:50,033 --> 01:30:51,952
- Give me the keys, I'll move it.
- It'll be all right.

1063
01:30:52,077 --> 01:30:54,079
- Wait out there.
- Oh, for Christ…

1064
01:30:54,204 --> 01:30:56,290
Give me a minute,
I've got to get something for you.

1065
01:31:00,961 --> 01:31:04,464
Fact six. Car licence SG13 7IU.

1066
01:31:10,846 --> 01:31:13,891
Look, wait a minute, will ya?

1067
01:31:16,602 --> 01:31:18,854
- We gotta get you out of here.
- Why?

1068
01:31:18,979 --> 01:31:21,899
Oh, man. Come on, Leonard.
How many times I gotta tell you?

1069
01:31:22,024 --> 01:31:24,443
- It's not safe for you to hang around.
- Why not?

1070
01:31:24,568 --> 01:31:27,863
Because that cop's looking for you.
I gotta get you a new identity,…

1071
01:31:27,988 --> 01:31:31,325
… some new clothes, a different car
would do for now. Put these on.

1072
01:31:31,450 --> 01:31:33,285
Whoa, whoa. What cop?

1073
01:31:33,410 --> 01:31:37,456
He's a bad cop. He's the one
that checked you into the Discount Inn.

1074
01:31:37,581 --> 01:31:41,460
He's been calling you for days, slipping
envelopes under your door, shit like that.

1075
01:31:41,585 --> 01:31:45,547
- How do you know this?
- He told me. He's been laughing at you.

1076
01:31:45,672 --> 01:31:47,049
- You're full of shit.
- No, I'm not.

1077
01:31:47,174 --> 01:31:49,176
He knows you're no good on the phone
so he's been calling you up.

1078
01:31:49,301 --> 01:31:51,261
Sometimes you don't answer the phone…

1079
01:31:51,386 --> 01:31:54,139
… so he slips shit under your door
to scare you into answering it,…

1080
01:31:54,264 --> 01:31:59,394
… giving you a line of crap about John G
being a local drug dealer. Jimmy Grants.

1081
01:31:59,520 --> 01:32:02,272
- Who's Jimmy Grants?
- Leonard, Jimmy's the drug dealer.

1082
01:32:02,397 --> 01:32:05,859
The cop wants to know how his operation
is run. He's got some score in mind.

1083
01:32:05,984 --> 01:32:08,487
- Somehow you're involved.
- How do you know him?

1084
01:32:08,612 --> 01:32:14,243
I'm a snitch. He's a cop from out of town.
The local boys put us together.

1085
01:32:14,409 --> 01:32:16,703
If he knew I was helping you,
he'd fucking kill me.

1086
01:32:16,828 --> 01:32:20,582
So take these clothes, put them on
and get the fuck out of here.

1087
01:32:20,707 --> 01:32:22,543
Come on, Leonard, just go.

1088
01:32:42,896 --> 01:32:44,773
You are full of shit.

1089
01:32:47,651 --> 01:32:49,695
Come by after. Natalie.

1090
01:32:50,404 --> 01:32:52,281
Ferdy's bar.

1091
01:33:32,696 --> 01:33:34,072
<font color="#40a040">[knocks on window]</font>

1092
01:33:34,198 --> 01:33:36,366
Hey, Jimmy.

1093
01:33:37,993 --> 01:33:41,038
I'm sorry, I, uh,
thought you were somebody else.

1094
01:33:41,496 --> 01:33:43,290
Sorry.

1095
01:33:43,415 --> 01:33:45,417
That's OK.

1096
01:33:59,223 --> 01:34:03,227
This Jimmy Grants deals drugs
out of the bar where his girlfriend works?

1097
01:34:03,644 --> 01:34:07,314
But he's not going to bring her along?
He'll come by himself, right?

1098
01:34:07,439 --> 01:34:11,318
I always figured the drugs angle
would be the best way to get him.

1099
01:34:11,568 --> 01:34:14,947
No, officer. I'm as ready as I'll ever be.

1100
01:34:15,072 --> 01:34:17,950
You're in the lobby?
What do you look like?

1101
01:34:19,284 --> 01:34:20,202
I'll be right there.

1102
01:35:03,370 --> 01:35:04,246
Lenny!

1103
01:35:06,540 --> 01:35:08,542
Officer Gammell?

1104
01:35:11,587 --> 01:35:13,589
Yeah. Come on.

1105
01:35:30,397 --> 01:35:33,317
- Hey, smile.
- Oh, don't, uh… Not here.

1106
01:35:34,193 --> 01:35:36,195
Over here.

1107
01:35:40,741 --> 01:35:43,410
Is it Officer or Lieutenant Gammell?

1108
01:35:43,493 --> 01:35:46,455
You know what?
Don't write Gammell, just Teddy.

1109
01:35:46,580 --> 01:35:49,166
- Why?
- I'm undercover.

1110
01:35:51,919 --> 01:35:54,630
This is the directions, where he's going.

1111
01:35:54,755 --> 01:35:57,591
- My number's on the bottom if you…
- You're not coming?

1112
01:35:57,716 --> 01:36:00,469
Nah, it wouldn't be appropriate.

1113
01:36:04,473 --> 01:36:07,142
Nice picture. I look thin.

1114
01:36:09,895 --> 01:36:11,271
Hey, Lenny!

1115
01:36:12,856 --> 01:36:14,233
Make him beg.

1116
01:37:36,899 --> 01:37:38,901
Teddy!

1117
01:37:41,069 --> 01:37:42,196
Hey, Teddy!

1118
01:37:45,282 --> 01:37:47,075
Teddy!

1119
01:37:50,287 --> 01:37:52,080
Jimmy.

1120
01:37:52,581 --> 01:37:55,792
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- You Jimmy Grants?

1121
01:37:55,918 --> 01:37:57,878
Expecting any other Jimmys,
memory man?

1122
01:37:58,003 --> 01:38:02,216
- Do you remember me?
- Yeah, I remember you.

1123
01:38:02,341 --> 01:38:04,718
Where the fuck's Teddy?

1124
01:38:04,843 --> 01:38:05,886
Well?

1125
01:38:09,598 --> 01:38:11,475
Motherfuck!

1126
01:38:11,600 --> 01:38:12,392
What are you doing?

1127
01:38:14,603 --> 01:38:15,771
Strip.

1128
01:38:15,896 --> 01:38:18,315
- You're making a big fucking mistake!
- Strip!

1129
01:38:19,942 --> 01:38:22,986
My associates are not the kind of people
you wanna piss off.

1130
01:38:23,111 --> 01:38:24,738
Don't say anything else.

1131
01:38:24,863 --> 01:38:27,824
- I knew I couldn't trust that fuck!
- Take it off.

1132
01:38:33,163 --> 01:38:35,165
Your pants, too.

1133
01:38:35,374 --> 01:38:37,793
- Why?
- I don't wanna get blood on them.

1134
01:38:37,918 --> 01:38:41,880
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait, wait, wait!
Did he tell you what I was bringing?

1135
01:38:42,005 --> 01:38:45,926
- Take your fuckin' pants off!
- I've got two hundred grand in the car!

1136
01:38:46,051 --> 01:38:48,720
- Just take it!
- You think you can bargain with me?

1137
01:38:48,804 --> 01:38:51,098
- Just take the money and walk away.
- I don't want your fucking money.

1138
01:38:51,223 --> 01:38:53,600
Then, what?

1139
01:38:53,725 --> 01:38:56,979
- What do you want from me?
- I want my fucking life back!

1140
01:40:28,487 --> 01:40:29,655
<font color="#40a040">[softly]</font> Sammy.

1141
01:40:36,495 --> 01:40:38,580
He said Sammy.
How does he know about Sammy?

1142
01:40:38,705 --> 01:40:40,707
Oh, fuck.

1143
01:41:00,602 --> 01:41:02,604
What have I done?

1144
01:41:03,939 --> 01:41:05,107
Hey, mister! I need help!

1145
01:41:05,232 --> 01:41:08,777
There's a guy in here, he's hurt bad.
We gotta get him to a doctor.

1146
01:41:08,902 --> 01:41:10,028
All right.

1147
01:41:11,321 --> 01:41:13,574
I don't know what happened.
I've got this memory thing.

1148
01:41:13,699 --> 01:41:16,618
- Do I know you?
- No. Don't worry, I'm a cop.

1149
01:41:16,743 --> 01:41:19,997
- Is he still breathing?
- Well, I don't know. Maybe.

1150
01:41:20,122 --> 01:41:25,085
- What the hell were you guys doing?
- I don't remember, I have this condition.

1151
01:41:25,210 --> 01:41:28,172
I hope it's not as serious as his
cos this guy's dead.

1152
01:41:28,672 --> 01:41:32,509
- Ow! Lenny! That shit kills!
- So you remember me now, huh?

1153
01:41:32,634 --> 01:41:37,222
- You are a fucking cop!
- And I'm the guy that helped you find him.

1154
01:41:37,347 --> 01:41:41,810
- Get up! Get up!
- Lenny, you got the wrong idea!

1155
01:41:44,730 --> 01:41:46,773
Who is that? He knew me.

1156
01:41:46,899 --> 01:41:49,568
Of course he did, he raped your wife,
he fucked up your brain.

1157
01:41:49,651 --> 01:41:51,653
Bullshit! He's not the guy.

1158
01:41:51,778 --> 01:41:55,616
His name is James F Grants. John G.
Check your tattoos.

1159
01:41:55,741 --> 01:41:58,410
- Why did he bring two hundred grand?
- What?

1160
01:42:00,454 --> 01:42:02,706
- What was it for?
- Amphetamines I told him I had.

1161
01:42:02,831 --> 01:42:06,376
- Is this a drug deal?
- No. Yeah, that and your thing.

1162
01:42:06,502 --> 01:42:09,963
Look, Jimmy's your guy. I figured
we'd make a few dollars on the side.

1163
01:42:10,088 --> 01:42:12,925
- How did he know me?
- The Discount Inn.

1164
01:42:13,050 --> 01:42:17,387
He dealt out of there. The guy at the front
desk let him know if anybody came round.

1165
01:42:17,513 --> 01:42:19,765
He called Jimmy
the minute he saw you taking a picture.

1166
01:42:19,890 --> 01:42:22,267
- You're fucking using me.
